      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T17:44:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "@ed@tanous.net, I\u0027ve updated the patch to remove the explicit SSL_set_tlsext_host_name() call.\n\nThe existing setCipherSuiteTLSext() function already calls SSL_set_tlsext_host_name() internally, so the explicit call was redundant. The SNI IP address is now set through the existing code path via setCipherSuiteTLSext().\n\nThe server-side routing logic remains the same - it uses the SNI value set by setCipherSuiteTLSext() to select between:\n\nOptional client cert context: Uses customer certificates (server.pem)\nRequired client cert context: Uses peer-to-peer BMC server certificates (server_bmc.pem from TPM)\nThis simplifies the implementation by leveraging existing infrastructure rather than adding redundant SNI setting code",
      "parentUuid": "52d6d381_6107281f",
      "revId": "3587d03538a1edb7ce0b4b640fc3ea5325ee37ec",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
